cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and semantic relationships between terms. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves measuring relatedness between terms in a document. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a new context type and relatedness measure. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it involves developing a measure that quantifies the document structure using multiple attributes and classes of weighted distance functions.
